00:16.773 --> 00:18.297
<i>BOY:
Listen.</i>

00:21.011 --> 00:22.808
<i>Can you hear it?</i>

00:25.648 --> 00:27.206
<i>The music.</i>

00:29.886 --> 00:32.150
<i>I can hear it everywhere.</i>

00:34.724 --> 00:36.487
<i>In the wind...</i>

00:38.128 --> 00:39.925
<i>...in the air...</i>

00:42.065 --> 00:43.862
<i>...in the light.</i>

00:49.606 --> 00:51.699
<i>It's all around us.</i>

01:01.551 --> 01:05.214
<i>All you have to do is open yourself up.</i>

01:15.732 --> 01:17.757
<i>All you have to do...</i>

01:18.835 --> 01:20.666
<i>...is listen.</i>

01:31.948 --> 01:34.576
[MARK MANCINA'S
"WHEATFIELDS" PLAYING]

02:10.419 --> 02:14.287
Hello, Porky. Where's your little friend?

02:14.456 --> 02:17.653
-I don't know, Mr. Mannix.
-Go find him or your big butt's mine.

02:19.328 --> 02:20.522
<i>AUGUST:
Where I've grown up--</i>

02:20.696 --> 02:21.720
Evan!

02:24.299 --> 02:25.323
PETER:
Evan!

02:25.501 --> 02:28.163
<i>--they tried to stop me
from hearing the music.</i>

02:32.341 --> 02:34.366
<i>But when I'm alone...</i>

02:36.678 --> 02:39.044
<i>...it builds up from inside me.</i>

02:41.416 --> 02:43.714
<i>And I think if I could learn
how to play it...</i>

02:48.624 --> 02:49.955
<i>...they might hear me.</i>

02:52.327 --> 02:54.557
<i>They would know I was theirs...</i>

02:56.031 --> 02:57.828
<i>...and find me.</i>

02:59.868 --> 03:01.859
MANNIX:
Knock, knock.

03:02.037 --> 03:04.096
BOY 1: Knock, knock.
MANNIX: Knock, knock.

03:04.273 --> 03:05.433
-Knock, knock.
BOY 2: Wake up.

03:05.607 --> 03:07.472
MANNIX:
Who's there? Who's there?

03:08.510 --> 03:11.673
Freak. Freak.

03:13.215 --> 03:16.412
-Said, knock, knock, freak.
-Who's there?

03:16.585 --> 03:19.418
Your long-lost mommy and daddy.

03:20.956 --> 03:22.617
Can you hear them?

03:23.625 --> 03:25.286
Yes.

03:29.765 --> 03:31.596
No, you can't.

03:32.401 --> 03:33.732
I can.

03:38.540 --> 03:41.236
You don't have no family.

03:41.944 --> 03:44.105
You can't hear anything.

03:44.580 --> 03:46.047
Say it.

03:48.083 --> 03:49.846
-Say it.
BOY 1: Say it. Say it.

03:50.018 --> 03:51.918
MANNIX: Say it.
BOY 2: Say it.

03:52.087 --> 03:53.213
MANNIX: Say it.
BOY 1: Say it.

03:53.388 --> 03:55.117
Say it.

03:56.158 --> 03:57.625
Yes...

03:58.360 --> 03:59.384
...I can.

04:01.463 --> 04:03.624
He doesn't hear anything.

04:04.266 --> 04:05.597
BOY 3:
Yeah.

04:06.969 --> 04:08.197
What is he?

04:09.705 --> 04:11.263
He's a freak.

04:14.943 --> 04:17.571
MANNIX: Sweet dreams, freaks.
BOY 2: Sleep tight.

04:17.745 --> 04:20.237
-Good night.
BOY 1: Don't let the bed bugs bite.

04:25.854 --> 04:28.118
<i>Sometimes the world
tries to knock it out of you.</i>

04:32.226 --> 04:34.217
<i>But I believe in music...</i>

04:34.395 --> 04:37.592
<i>...the way that some people
believe in fairy tales.</i>

04:49.910 --> 04:55.405
<i>I like to imagine that what I hear
came from my mother and father.</i>

05:13.701 --> 05:15.862
<i>Maybe the notes I hear...</i>

05:16.037 --> 05:20.804
<i>...are the same ones they heard
the night they met.</i>

05:22.410 --> 05:25.538
<i>Maybe that's how they found each other.</i>

05:28.416 --> 05:30.646
<i>Maybe that's how they'll find me.</i>

05:30.818 --> 05:31.807
[BANGING ON DOOR]

05:31.986 --> 05:34.318
MAN:
Louis. Louie, where are you?

05:34.488 --> 05:37.150
-Lyla? She's here. What are you doing?
LYLA: Dad.

05:37.325 --> 05:40.783
They're waiting for us.
Hey, sit up straight, please.

05:40.961 --> 05:43.521
Where are you, baby bro?

05:43.698 --> 05:46.963
We didn't follow you from San Francisco
to play for free, man. Yeah?

05:47.134 --> 05:50.467
We need this one, baby bro. All right?
I need this one.

05:50.638 --> 05:52.469
THOMAS:
Don't forget to smile and look relaxed.

05:54.375 --> 05:56.570
All right, not that relaxed.
Come on, come on.

06:00.047 --> 06:02.811
<i>I believe that, once upon a time...</i>

06:03.451 --> 06:05.180
<i>...long ago...</i>

06:06.487 --> 06:09.888
<i>...they heard the music and followed it.</i>

06:15.830 --> 06:20.858
[MARK MANCINA'S
"MAIN TITLE" PLAYING]

06:33.781 --> 06:40.744
[SYMPHONY PLAYING JOHANN SEBASTIAN
BACH'S "PRELUDE FROM PARTITA NO. 3"]

07:07.915 --> 07:10.907
[BAND PLAYING
JOHN ONDRASIK'S "BREAK"]

07:18.159 --> 07:19.751
<i>[SINGING]
I break</i>

07:20.894 --> 07:22.589
<i>I borrow</i>

07:23.630 --> 07:25.564
<i>I live</i>

07:26.366 --> 07:28.926
<i>I lose</i>

07:29.102 --> 07:30.660
<i>I pray</i>

07:31.938 --> 07:34.498
<i>I'm hollow</i>

07:34.674 --> 07:39.111
<i>I'm dead confused</i>

07:39.679 --> 07:42.409
<i>I'll find you</i>

07:46.085 --> 07:51.421
<i>Once you're here, you're never gone
Once you're here, you're never gone</i>

07:51.591 --> 07:57.086
<i>Fallen from a night of cold
A piece of me that I can't hold</i>

07:57.263 --> 08:02.462
<i>I love you as I lose you more
I break outside this open door</i>

08:02.635 --> 08:07.538
<i>Catch me as I wash away
You'll catch me as I wash away</i>

08:08.174 --> 08:10.665
<i>Well, catch me as I wash away</i>

08:16.216 --> 08:17.740
<i>Oh, oh</i>

08:17.917 --> 08:19.817
<i>Oh</i>

08:21.788 --> 08:23.483
<i>Yeah</i>

08:24.557 --> 08:26.024
<i>Don't</i>

08:26.192 --> 08:29.958
<i>Don't wait, don't wait</i>

08:32.030 --> 08:34.158
<i>I break</i>

08:34.868 --> 08:38.770
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

09:00.760 --> 09:02.625
[DANIEL LEVY'S "THE SWAN"
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

09:02.862 --> 09:05.990
MAN: Not bad, Connelly. Not bad.
-Thanks very much, man.

09:06.165 --> 09:07.393
Where's the main man?

09:08.167 --> 09:10.362
Goddamn it, Louis. Just wait, man.

09:12.138 --> 09:15.699
Louis? Louis, wait up, man.

09:18.912 --> 09:22.040
LIZZY:
Girls, we are going to a party tonight.

09:22.215 --> 09:24.445
It's a full moon,
you know what that means, right?

09:24.617 --> 09:26.209
[WOMEN SCREAM]

09:27.887 --> 09:30.185
[MARK MANCINA'S "CONFESSIONS
OF LOVE" PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

09:36.596 --> 09:38.188
LIZZY:
Lyla.

09:48.775 --> 09:51.175
[HARMONICA PLAYS "MOONDANCE"
IN DISTANCE]

10:22.641 --> 10:25.109
LOUIS:
It's a great sound, isn't it?

10:26.578 --> 10:28.637
What are you doing?

10:28.814 --> 10:30.441
Listening.

10:33.151 --> 10:34.482
What are you doing?

10:37.022 --> 10:41.618
-I just came up here to, um....
-Get away?

10:46.698 --> 10:48.427
Have a seat.

10:48.600 --> 10:51.967
Come on, be brave.

10:52.137 --> 10:54.105
Front row, center.

11:19.531 --> 11:21.123
Can you hear that?

11:21.867 --> 11:23.698
What is that?

11:24.136 --> 11:25.865
It's a wish.

11:34.846 --> 11:36.973
Now, what does that sound like?

11:38.150 --> 11:42.883
<i>[SINGING] Well, it's a marvelous night
For a moondance</i>

11:43.055 --> 11:46.991
<i>With the stars up above in your eyes</i>

11:47.893 --> 11:51.954
<i>A fantabulous night to make romance</i>

11:52.431 --> 11:56.891
<i>'Neath the cover of October skies</i>

11:57.969 --> 11:59.960
When I was a young fellow...

12:00.806 --> 12:03.104
...I used to talk to the moon.

12:04.409 --> 12:06.036
Are you making that up?

12:08.213 --> 12:10.204
God, I haven't done that in a long time.

12:13.452 --> 12:16.046
Does it ever talk back?

12:17.622 --> 12:19.681
Well, it used to.

12:21.393 --> 12:24.851
Now I just find myself on a roof
talking to myself...

12:25.030 --> 12:27.521
...like a loon.

12:29.801 --> 12:33.828
Just out here on me own.

12:36.274 --> 12:38.105
Well, I'm here.

12:40.612 --> 12:42.671
Yes, you are.

12:51.523 --> 12:53.047
I'm Louis.

12:55.527 --> 12:57.222
Lyla.

12:57.896 --> 13:00.057
So, what's your story, Lyla?

13:02.433 --> 13:04.799
I don't know. I'm just, um....

13:07.671 --> 13:09.901
I'm just me.

13:16.747 --> 13:18.647
What are you looking at?

13:19.984 --> 13:21.474
You.

14:08.199 --> 14:09.962
[MARK MANCINA'S
"5-NOTE WINDCHIMES" PLAYING]

14:18.776 --> 14:20.300
MAN:
Next.

14:21.378 --> 14:23.312
What did he want? What did you say?

14:23.480 --> 14:26.176
You know, same old junk. New guy.

14:28.085 --> 14:29.609
My name is Mr. Jeffries.

14:29.787 --> 14:32.881
I'm with Child Services
for the state of New York.

14:33.057 --> 14:34.581
[WIND CHIMES TINKLE]

14:34.758 --> 14:36.783
Okay, Evan.

14:36.961 --> 14:41.398
Born December 17th, 1995.

14:41.565 --> 14:44.898
Legal adoption to New York Children's.

14:45.970 --> 14:48.029
[WHISTLING]

14:49.073 --> 14:50.700
How long have you been here, Evan?

14:51.041 --> 14:52.906
Eleven years and sixteen days.

14:55.179 --> 14:56.703
I've been counting.

14:58.115 --> 14:59.582
That's a long time.

15:00.184 --> 15:03.119
-How do you do that?
-Do what?

15:03.287 --> 15:05.380
[BLOWS]

15:07.958 --> 15:10.426
Well, it's just imitating the wind chimes.

15:10.594 --> 15:12.255
[BLOWS]

15:13.063 --> 15:15.293
[WHISTLES]

15:15.466 --> 15:18.060
[WHISTLES]

15:19.270 --> 15:20.794
[CHUCKLES]

15:23.874 --> 15:26.707
You don't wanna be placed
with a real family?

15:26.877 --> 15:30.142
-I have a family.
-Yes, you do.

15:30.314 --> 15:33.647
I mean, you have parents and all,
but they don't live with you.

15:33.817 --> 15:34.977
Not now.

15:35.419 --> 15:39.219
But still,
you don't have contact with them.

15:39.390 --> 15:42.848
-Yes, I do.
-You do?

15:46.897 --> 15:48.125
What, do they call you?

15:50.600 --> 15:51.828
Come and visit you?

15:52.302 --> 15:53.564
-Send--?
-I....

15:56.439 --> 15:58.600
I don't wanna be sent away.

16:01.577 --> 16:03.511
I understand.

16:05.381 --> 16:08.077
You see, there's a lot of children...

16:08.251 --> 16:10.947
...who are scared
that if they leave their first home...

16:11.120 --> 16:13.452
...their parents would never
be able to find them.

16:14.557 --> 16:16.115
Right?

16:16.726 --> 16:18.455
But see, my job is to make sure...

16:18.628 --> 16:22.064
...that nothing like that
will ever happen to you.

16:22.231 --> 16:25.359
So there's nothing to be scared of.

16:26.970 --> 16:28.665
Thank you.

16:34.978 --> 16:37.606
I'm gonna do something I never do.

16:38.815 --> 16:41.010
This is my number.

16:41.184 --> 16:45.382
If you ever need to talk to me,
about anything...

16:46.990 --> 16:48.480
...you call.

16:48.658 --> 16:51.149
Think about what I said too.

16:51.761 --> 16:55.788
There's a whole world out there
with millions of wind chimes.

16:56.399 --> 16:57.730
I know.

17:05.340 --> 17:06.672
You can go now.

17:17.453 --> 17:20.148
<i>PETER: Mannix says we're never
gonna see our real parents again.</i>

17:20.323 --> 17:22.450
Mannix is a big liar.

17:23.259 --> 17:26.422
Yeah, I know. But what if he's right?

17:26.596 --> 17:29.793
I mean, what if they don't ever come?

17:29.966 --> 17:32.901
Hardly remember what my mom
looks like, you know?

17:33.369 --> 17:39.535
Well, if they don't find us,
we'll just have to go find them.

17:45.281 --> 17:48.876
[VAN MORRISON'S "MOONDANCE"
PLAYING]

18:12.642 --> 18:13.734
[CORK POPS]

18:13.910 --> 18:14.899
[LYLA SCREAMS]

18:15.078 --> 18:16.306
[MEN CHEER]

18:16.946 --> 18:17.935
[LAUGHING]

18:19.315 --> 18:20.373
LYLA: Oh, my God.
-Morning.

18:20.550 --> 18:21.915
-How's it going?
LYLA: Oh, my God.

18:22.085 --> 18:23.382
Get away.

18:23.553 --> 18:24.781
[LAUGHING]

18:24.954 --> 18:26.182
LYLA:
I have to go.

18:26.355 --> 18:28.448
-Let me walk you home.
-No.

18:28.624 --> 18:30.592
LYLA:
My dad's waiting at the Sherry. I--

18:31.027 --> 18:33.689
I've never done this before.
I'm in so much trouble.

18:33.863 --> 18:34.887
Hey, hey.

18:35.064 --> 18:36.122
MEN:
Woo!

18:36.299 --> 18:38.324
Meet me here at 10:00 by the arch.

18:38.501 --> 18:39.660
[MARSHALL LAUGHING]

18:39.835 --> 18:42.269
LOUIS: Say yes.
-Put him out of his misery. Say yes.

18:42.437 --> 18:43.927
-Say yes.
-Say it.

18:44.106 --> 18:45.767
Say yes.

18:49.377 --> 18:50.901
After you.

18:51.880 --> 18:53.313
I'll take that as a yes.

18:57.819 --> 19:01.812
You are gonna be in so much trouble.
You should have left your dad a note.

19:01.990 --> 19:04.686
Yeah, ransom note.
You know what? I don't even care.

19:04.860 --> 19:08.125
I just had the most incredible night
of my life.

19:08.296 --> 19:09.593
Taxi!

19:09.764 --> 19:13.757
[MARK MANCINA'S
"WASHINGTON SQUARE" PLAYING]

19:16.805 --> 19:19.365
MARSHALL:
Louis. She ain't coming.

19:19.541 --> 19:22.704
Oh, man. One girl?

19:22.878 --> 19:25.472
Come on, we're gonna miss the flight.

19:28.283 --> 19:32.276
-Taxi!
MARSHALL: Louis. Where you going, Louis?

19:34.489 --> 19:35.649
Excuse me.

19:37.259 --> 19:38.920
MARSHALL:
Louie.

19:40.128 --> 19:41.459
THOMAS:
You are not going anywhere.

19:41.930 --> 19:44.626
-Lyla!
LYLA: Dad, I'm not going with you.

19:44.799 --> 19:47.529
-Lyla, you listen to me.
-No.

19:47.702 --> 19:50.398
-Don't you dare walk away.
LYLA: I'm not going with you.

19:57.646 --> 19:59.739
LOUIS:
Lyla!

20:05.287 --> 20:08.051
THOMAS:
Get in the car right now.

20:11.092 --> 20:13.492
Lyla! Lyla!

20:26.675 --> 20:28.302
MARSHALL:
Louis.

20:31.513 --> 20:34.346
Do you remember what Da used to say
about princesses? Huh?

20:34.516 --> 20:38.577
They're always looking for their prince.
And you ain't no prince, brother.

20:39.821 --> 20:40.947
How would you know?

20:41.957 --> 20:43.857
What am I gonna do now?

20:58.106 --> 21:00.301
<i>I know they're out there somewhere.</i>

21:01.243 --> 21:04.440
[VIBRATING AND BUZZING]

21:04.613 --> 21:07.912
[MARK MANCINA'S "WIRES" PLAYING]

21:14.689 --> 21:17.089
<i>I don't know where it comes from...</i>

21:20.762 --> 21:22.559
<i>...but it's what I hold on to.</i>

21:26.968 --> 21:29.094
<i>And I can't let go.</i>

21:29.270 --> 21:30.601
[WIND WHISTLES]

21:33.574 --> 21:34.973
<i>Somewhere inside me...</i>

21:36.410 --> 21:39.106
<i>...I know that they always wanted me.</i>

21:41.482 --> 21:43.882
<i>Maybe they just got lost.</i>

21:45.219 --> 21:48.450
<i>LOUIS [SINGING]:
Walking through wintertime</i>

21:48.622 --> 21:51.955
<i>When the stars all shine</i>

21:55.829 --> 21:59.321
<i>The angel on the stairs</i>

22:02.269 --> 22:05.761
<i>Will tell you I was there</i>

22:05.939 --> 22:07.304
[CELLO PLAYING MARK MANCINA'S
"CELLO OVERLUDE"]

22:07.474 --> 22:10.932
<i>Under the front porch light</i>

22:11.111 --> 22:13.978
<i>On a mystery night</i>

22:20.354 --> 22:21.582
<i>I been sitting</i>

22:21.755 --> 22:25.953
<i>Watching life pass from the sidelines</i>

22:27.094 --> 22:29.153
<i>Been waiting for a dream</i>

22:29.330 --> 22:33.494
<i>To seep in through my blinds</i>

22:33.667 --> 22:36.158
<i>I wondered what might happen</i>

22:36.337 --> 22:38.999
<i>If I left this all behind</i>

22:39.807 --> 22:42.867
<i>Would the wind be at my back?</i>

22:43.043 --> 22:46.945
<i>Could I get you off my mind</i>

22:49.083 --> 22:50.141
<i>This time?</i>

22:50.351 --> 22:52.876
<i>LOUIS:
What's the point in singing, Marshall?</i>

22:53.754 --> 22:55.381
<i>She's not gonna hear me.</i>

22:56.223 --> 22:59.192
<i>I'm leaving the band.
I'm sorry, Marshall.</i>

22:59.360 --> 23:01.328
<i>MARSHALL:
Don't quit on us, Louis.</i>

23:03.397 --> 23:06.696
<i>[SINGING]
The things I left behind</i>

23:07.267 --> 23:09.701
THOMAS: Everything you've given up,
everything I've given up--

23:10.070 --> 23:11.799
<i>[SINGING]
Have melted in my mind</i>

23:11.972 --> 23:14.372
I can't do it. I'm sorry, Frank.
I can't do it, man.

23:14.541 --> 23:16.236
-Listen to me. Listen to me.
-No!

23:16.410 --> 23:18.571
-You know what I mean? I don't know...
-Dad!

23:18.746 --> 23:20.236
...how to approach this problem.

23:20.414 --> 23:22.405
I mean, where are you
gonna put the baby?

23:22.583 --> 23:25.609
And what about this boy?
He's not here now. He's not here now.

23:25.786 --> 23:27.185
-I'm leaving.
-You can't leave.

23:27.354 --> 23:30.414
-Where you going, then?
-Just let me go. Will you just let me go?

23:31.024 --> 23:33.015
<i>LOUIS [SINGING]:
Would the wind be at my back?</i>

23:34.294 --> 23:37.752
<i>Could I get you off my mind</i>

23:37.931 --> 23:40.058
MARSHALL: Louis.
THOMAS: Lyla.

23:40.234 --> 23:41.667
<i>This time?</i>

23:43.303 --> 23:44.702
Hey, Louis.

23:46.073 --> 23:47.540
THOMAS:
Lyla.

23:48.142 --> 23:49.370
[SCREAMS]

23:49.543 --> 23:50.532
[TIRES SCREECH]

23:50.711 --> 23:52.474
[THUDS]

23:54.214 --> 23:55.943
[MARK MANCINA'S
"HOSPITAL PT. 1 " PLAYING]

24:10.998 --> 24:12.659
WOMAN:
We have fetal distress.

24:14.635 --> 24:16.626
Baby's heart rate is falling.

24:19.038 --> 24:20.699
It's falling.

24:49.302 --> 24:51.065
I'm sorry.

24:55.808 --> 24:57.673
He's gone.

26:01.374 --> 26:03.638
MAN: Picked him up on the thruway
outside of Montrose.

26:03.809 --> 26:06.869
Just wandering down the road.
Said he's following the music.

26:07.046 --> 26:09.708
The moon told him to.
Yeah. Kid's a space cadet.

26:12.785 --> 26:14.446
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

26:15.621 --> 26:18.089
Look, I got a busy day ahead of me.

26:19.225 --> 26:21.523
All right, big guy, out you go.

26:21.694 --> 26:23.787
This Jeffries guy
wasn't in his office yet...

26:23.963 --> 26:26.557
...so I left him a message
to pick you up right here.

26:26.732 --> 26:28.393
AUGUST: Okay.
-Here. Hold on.

26:28.568 --> 26:31.696
Don't lose it. If he doesn't show
in an hour, give him another call.

26:31.871 --> 26:33.532
You can handle that, right?

26:33.706 --> 26:35.264
-Yeah.
-You got any money?

26:35.708 --> 26:39.735
Here's 12 bucks.
Damn, kid, put it in your pocket.

26:39.912 --> 26:41.675
See you.

26:55.194 --> 26:57.492
[TRAINS CLICKING ON TRACKS]

27:00.499 --> 27:02.091
[TRAIN HORN BLOWS]

27:04.770 --> 27:06.635
[SCREECHING]

27:20.218 --> 27:24.177
[HORNS HONK, TIRES SCREECH
AND FOOTSTEPS TAP]

27:26.758 --> 27:28.783
[HIP HOP MUSIC PLAYS
ON STEREO]

27:34.799 --> 27:37.324
[WHISTLE BLOWS, HORN HONKS
AND DOG BARKS]

27:46.111 --> 27:47.476
[BELL RINGING]

27:47.646 --> 27:48.670
[THUDDING]

27:56.655 --> 27:58.782
[MARK MANCINA'S
"UNION SQUARE" PLAYING]

28:34.159 --> 28:35.148
[HORN HONKS]

28:35.326 --> 28:36.793
[GASPS]

28:39.230 --> 28:41.027
[GRUNTS]

28:42.534 --> 28:44.195
MAN:
Get on the sidewalk!

28:54.179 --> 28:56.477
[HORNS HONKING AND SIRENS WAILING]

29:04.222 --> 29:06.747
<i>BOY [SINGING]:
Para bailar la bamba</i>

29:06.925 --> 29:09.189
[GIRLS SINGING]

29:11.896 --> 29:16.833
<i>Give me your money</i>

29:17.001 --> 29:21.665
<i>Come here, sweet honey</i>

29:21.840 --> 29:25.298
<i>Come here, baby</i>

29:27.078 --> 29:28.238
Yeah.

29:29.280 --> 29:32.443
[PLAYING ALI DEE'S
"MY COUNTRY 'TIS OF THEE"]

29:46.798 --> 29:50.564
Okay, citizen. You paid. Any requests?

29:50.735 --> 29:52.202
AUGUST:
No.

29:53.638 --> 29:55.003
Alrighty, then.

29:57.342 --> 30:01.471
<i>[SINGING]
Father, hear me when I</i>

30:01.645 --> 30:03.943
<i>Call your name</i>

30:04.515 --> 30:08.849
<i>I need you to answer me now</i>

30:09.019 --> 30:12.921
<i>Father, here I am</i>

30:13.090 --> 30:16.025
<i>Weak in your sight</i>

30:16.193 --> 30:20.027
<i>Can you rescue me now?</i>

30:20.197 --> 30:26.295
<i>I'm crying out
Can't figure it out on my own</i>

30:28.605 --> 30:31.904
Back off. Away, away. Yo, son,
you're messing with my equilibrium.

30:32.075 --> 30:35.340
Nobody touches this instrument but me.
Roxy's my girl.

30:35.512 --> 30:38.106
Son, we done here,
so why don't you go find your mommy.

30:38.582 --> 30:41.949
-I don't know where she is.
-Good, that's just great. Uh....

30:42.119 --> 30:44.178
Cops show up around 6.
Tell them you're AWOL.

30:44.354 --> 30:46.254
They'll send you back
where you come from.

30:46.423 --> 30:47.788
I don't wanna go back there.

30:48.625 --> 30:50.115
Well, good.

30:50.294 --> 30:52.694
This day's been a bust anyway. I'm out.

31:03.140 --> 31:06.906
[MARK MANCINA'S
"FOLLOWING ARTHUR" PLAYING]

31:14.284 --> 31:15.342
What?

31:17.621 --> 31:19.248
I don't have a place to stay.

31:20.090 --> 31:22.581
Do I look like a real-estate tycoon
to you?

31:26.196 --> 31:27.993
How many dead presidents you got?

31:28.565 --> 31:30.863
Nuggets? Shorts?

31:31.034 --> 31:32.433
Show me the money.

31:37.207 --> 31:41.507
-Are you thinking what I'm thinking?
-No, I'm thinking something else.

31:43.747 --> 31:45.908
I'm gonna let you buy me a pizza.

32:01.531 --> 32:05.365
I've been doing this for 10 years, Bob.
I said 10 percent.

32:06.536 --> 32:08.936
We need to close the deal.
Hold on a second.

32:09.106 --> 32:12.337
No. We said 10 percent.

32:13.243 --> 32:16.235
Yeah, well, it makes the world go round,
doesn't it, Bob?

32:17.214 --> 32:19.580
Just get me the 10 percent, will you?

32:19.750 --> 32:21.240
Thanks.

32:21.985 --> 32:23.350
[SIGHS]

32:25.122 --> 32:28.353
MAN: Need anything, sir?
-Do you know any hit men?

32:28.525 --> 32:31.085
I do know a bass player
might be able to help you out.

32:31.261 --> 32:33.286
Likes to get in fights with lead singers.

32:35.465 --> 32:36.591
Nick?

32:38.368 --> 32:40.336
What are you doing, man?

32:41.872 --> 32:44.773
Still driving. Paying off
those wedding bills from last year.

32:44.942 --> 32:47.432
Oh, fair play to you. Oh, she's a nice girl.

32:48.844 --> 32:50.573
So you playing at all?

32:51.013 --> 32:52.173
Nope.

32:52.949 --> 32:55.474
Why the hell not? Your fingers fall off?

32:55.651 --> 32:57.448
Well, you move on.

32:59.722 --> 33:02.691
What about the lads?
Seen any of them lately?

33:04.026 --> 33:05.960
We still mess around...

33:06.128 --> 33:10.087
...but the Connelly Brothers never really
bounced back minus one brother.

33:14.603 --> 33:16.127
You seen Marshall lately?

33:17.073 --> 33:18.540
Have you?

33:18.708 --> 33:20.972
[VAN MORRISON'S
"MAGIC TIME" PLAYING]

33:21.744 --> 33:23.336
It's my birthday on Saturday.

33:23.946 --> 33:26.972
Session's at my place.
Come, bring your girlfriend.

33:27.850 --> 33:29.943
It's great seeing you, man.

33:30.119 --> 33:33.919
Reminds me of New York.
The good old days, eh?

33:34.290 --> 33:36.417
[SIRENS WAILING]

33:40.997 --> 33:42.988
[LYLA HUMMING BEETHOVEN'S
"FUR ELISE"]

33:43.165 --> 33:44.723
GIRL:
I know.

33:44.900 --> 33:47.130
I know.

33:47.303 --> 33:50.704
-I know. Okay, I don't know.
-Oh!

33:50.906 --> 33:54.103
"Fur Elise" by Beethoven.
And you should know that one.

33:54.276 --> 33:56.335
Oh, yeah.

33:56.512 --> 33:58.980
Will you be our teacher forever,
Miss Novacek?

33:59.148 --> 34:02.140
Well, at least until your old teacher
comes back.

34:02.318 --> 34:05.583
But only if you call me...?

34:05.755 --> 34:07.985
-Lyla.
-That's right.

34:08.157 --> 34:09.623
You're crazy, Miss Novacek.

34:09.792 --> 34:11.054
WOMAN: Megan.
-Got everything?

34:13.228 --> 34:14.924
<i>-Okay.
-Bye.</i>

34:15.097 --> 34:16.893
[MARK MANCINA'S
"ELEVEN YEARS LATER" PLAYING]

34:17.333 --> 34:19.893
Hi, sweetie.

34:20.436 --> 34:22.427
Did you have a good day?

34:23.839 --> 34:25.033
Thanks.

34:25.206 --> 34:26.400
LIZZY: There you are.
-Hey.

34:26.574 --> 34:30.272
Okay, now, before you say no....
Okay, picture this.

34:30.446 --> 34:34.678
You on stage, me accompanying,
thousands of people.

34:34.850 --> 34:36.317
-Liz.
-The New York Philharmonic.

34:36.485 --> 34:39.318
I just got the invite. They want you back.

34:39.487 --> 34:42.217
It's just one night,
but they want you back.

34:43.793 --> 34:45.954
I don't wanna be up there.

34:46.128 --> 34:47.618
Lyla....

34:48.431 --> 34:50.695
When are you gonna let yourself
be happy again?

34:50.866 --> 34:53.232
I am happy.

34:54.036 --> 34:57.369
I'm talking about
when everyone else goes home.

35:04.346 --> 35:06.177
Look....

35:06.348 --> 35:08.873
I know. Okay? I know.

35:10.419 --> 35:11.750
Just think about it.

35:11.921 --> 35:16.551
I mean, you're a music teacher
who doesn't play music anymore.

35:17.026 --> 35:18.926
Call me crazy.

35:19.095 --> 35:20.722
Okay, Crazy.

35:20.896 --> 35:23.456
-I'll see you at home, okay?
-All right.

35:34.810 --> 35:37.300
ARTHUR:
No, I ain't got no daddy.

35:38.813 --> 35:40.075
See, my pops is a drunk.

35:40.248 --> 35:43.843
And my mama, she took off
with this crackhead named Little Jesus.

35:44.018 --> 35:47.283
But, you know, he wasn't no little Jesus,
you know what I'm saying?

35:47.455 --> 35:48.479
[BILLIE HOLIDAY'S
"GOD BLESS THE CHILD" PLAYING]

35:48.656 --> 35:50.851
No, they never gave a damn about me.

35:51.025 --> 35:54.927
Come on, man. This is us right here.

35:57.031 --> 35:59.966
-I've been with Wizard for years.
AUGUST: Who's Wizard?

36:00.135 --> 36:02.501
ARTHUR: Oh, he's a real piece of work,
that's what he is.

36:02.670 --> 36:05.230
His real name's Maxwell Wallace.

36:05.406 --> 36:08.534
He took me in.
He said that I was an investment.

36:08.710 --> 36:11.804
He gave me Roxy here.
He bought it in the old days.

36:12.247 --> 36:15.580
Well, he really didn't buy it.
Guess you'd kind of say he found it.

36:15.750 --> 36:17.047
All right, he stole it.

36:17.218 --> 36:19.379
Wizard?
He gave me his place at the Square.

36:19.554 --> 36:22.045
My parents? They ain't gave me nothing.

36:24.626 --> 36:27.527
We all gonna be big stars someday.

36:28.530 --> 36:31.727
MAN: What's the password?
-Open the damn door already.

36:33.034 --> 36:34.797
You're getting on my nerves with that.

36:39.274 --> 36:41.299
Okay, follow me.

36:41.476 --> 36:44.570
[MARK MANCINA'S
"WIZARD'S LAIR" PLAYING]

36:44.746 --> 36:47.681
What's your name again?
It's Evan, right?

36:49.083 --> 36:51.449
Yo, this is our home, son.

36:51.619 --> 36:53.519
It's kind of crazy in here,
so stay on your feet.

36:53.688 --> 36:55.280
[BOY YELLS]

36:56.991 --> 36:58.151
Watch out.

36:58.326 --> 37:01.523
Yeah, I've been living here for a while.
Come on, man.

37:01.696 --> 37:03.755
Hey, check it out.

37:03.932 --> 37:05.092
-How much you make?
BOY 1: Ten dollars.

37:05.266 --> 37:07.200
ARTHUR: You lying. Let me see.
BOY 1: I am not lying.

37:07.368 --> 37:09.336
ARTHUR: What did I tell you about that?
-Boo!

37:10.605 --> 37:11.594
[BABBLING]

37:11.773 --> 37:14.674
BOY 2: Hey, it's Arthur.
ARTHUR: I'll be laughing at your funeral.

37:14.842 --> 37:16.901
BOY 1: I'm gonna go play basketball.
ARTHUR: All clear.

37:17.078 --> 37:22.607
<i>[SINGING] My life, the sky
Like a feather I'll fly</i>

37:23.384 --> 37:26.046
ARTHUR: Man, you should've knocked him
in his head, son.

37:26.554 --> 37:29.853
[PLAYING IMPACT REPERTORY THEATRE'S
"WIZARD'S THEATER SONG"]

37:36.965 --> 37:38.796
BOY 3:
Shoot it, shoot it, shoot it!

37:43.738 --> 37:45.137
Pizza!

37:50.245 --> 37:52.304
Pizza, pizza, pizza.

38:06.728 --> 38:08.127
GIRL 1:
Don't make me come up there.

38:08.296 --> 38:10.355
BOY 4: Yo, you better hurry
before Wizard shows.

38:10.531 --> 38:13.091
He'll be pissed
if he's seen you bought a pie.

38:13.468 --> 38:15.129
I ain't take no family money.

38:15.303 --> 38:16.600
Citizen bought it.

38:19.907 --> 38:22.603
<i>Hola, music lovers.</i>

38:22.777 --> 38:24.608
Wow, while the cat's away....

38:25.446 --> 38:26.810
Oh.

38:26.980 --> 38:28.277
Who likes pizza?

38:30.517 --> 38:31.814
Who did this?

38:33.420 --> 38:34.682
Arthur?

38:40.694 --> 38:42.753
-What is he?
-He's a damn fool.

38:42.929 --> 38:45.363
He's a damn fool.

38:45.532 --> 38:47.159
-He's gonna get it good.
-Shh.

38:47.334 --> 38:49.165
What are you, Arthur?

38:49.670 --> 38:51.604
I'm a real piece of work, Wizard.

38:53.273 --> 38:54.968
You're on thin ice.

38:55.475 --> 38:59.468
I didn't take no family money.
He bought it.

39:04.785 --> 39:06.184
What?

39:06.553 --> 39:07.850
You look crazy.

39:09.489 --> 39:10.615
I am crazy.

39:10.791 --> 39:12.725
[SCREAMS]

39:13.994 --> 39:15.393
See?

39:16.263 --> 39:17.321
Come here.

39:20.200 --> 39:21.724
Now!

39:23.036 --> 39:24.469
Come on.

39:27.808 --> 39:30.743
-What's your name?
-Evan, sir.

39:31.545 --> 39:32.876
What are you doing here?

39:33.680 --> 39:35.477
I followed the music.

39:40.954 --> 39:44.219
Where did you pick this one up,
Arthur, Bellevue?

39:48.328 --> 39:50.694
You never played a note in your life.

39:50.864 --> 39:52.889
Do you know what music is?

39:54.568 --> 39:58.698
It's God's little reminder there's
something else besides us in this universe.

39:59.239 --> 40:04.871
Harmonic connection between
all living beings everywhere, even the stars.

40:05.612 --> 40:07.512
Is this a school?

40:07.681 --> 40:10.912
Yeah, the school of
Screw You and Take All Your Damn Money.

40:11.084 --> 40:12.949
-Yeah.
-Yeah, we're top of the class.

40:13.120 --> 40:14.485
Not!

40:16.890 --> 40:18.380
It's a business.

40:21.027 --> 40:23.621
-Pockets.
GIRL 2: Okay, let's go.

40:23.797 --> 40:25.424
-Let's go, let's go.
WALLACE: Pockets.

40:26.299 --> 40:27.425
BOY 1:
Oh, man. Get up.

40:27.601 --> 40:29.592
[CHATTERING]

40:31.571 --> 40:32.799
WALLACE:
Peanut, well done.

40:34.074 --> 40:35.735
I got eyes in the back of my head.

40:36.710 --> 40:38.575
<i>Good job. Gracias, amigo.</i>

40:38.745 --> 40:40.975
Chain is only as strong...

40:41.415 --> 40:42.712
...as its weakest link.

40:45.419 --> 40:46.909
Come on, Arthur.

40:47.254 --> 40:48.812
That's chump change.

40:48.989 --> 40:52.322
You got Washington Square.
That was my spot for 10 years.

40:56.463 --> 40:59.591
Go ahead, before I change my mind.

41:03.904 --> 41:06.065
You kids are gonna put me
in the poorhouse.

41:07.040 --> 41:09.975
All right, little mice,
scurry back to your holes. Go, go.

41:12.612 --> 41:15.445
Harmonic dreams, sweet children.

41:23.422 --> 41:25.322
[PLAYING VAN MORRISON'S
"MOONDANCE" ON HARMONICA]

42:05.664 --> 42:10.158
[PLAYING MARK MANCINA'S
"BARI IMPROV"]

43:45.531 --> 43:47.658
ARTHUR:
Roxanne. Man, I'm gonna kill him.

44:15.994 --> 44:17.928
WALLACE:
You know what's out there?

44:18.563 --> 44:20.690
A series of higher tones.

44:20.865 --> 44:22.389
It's arranged by nature.

44:22.567 --> 44:26.628
It's governed by the laws of physics
of the whole universe.

44:28.039 --> 44:30.439
It's an overtone, it's an energy,
it's a wavelength.

44:30.608 --> 44:35.136
And if you're not riding it, good Lordy,
you'll never hear it.

44:35.313 --> 44:37.338
Where do you think it comes from?

44:39.150 --> 44:40.447
What I hear.

44:41.052 --> 44:44.544
I think it comes from all around you, really.
I mean, it's--

44:44.722 --> 44:46.553
Comes through us, some of us.

44:48.793 --> 44:51.853
It's invisible, but-- But you feel it.

44:52.797 --> 44:54.560
So only some of us can hear it?

44:56.200 --> 44:58.168
Only some of us are listening.

45:00.972 --> 45:03.304
Do you think my parents are listening?

45:04.175 --> 45:06.143
I hear you, kid.

45:09.113 --> 45:10.102
Like:

45:10.281 --> 45:11.646
[STRUMS GUITAR]

45:12.216 --> 45:13.808
Yeah.

45:17.755 --> 45:19.382
WOMAN:
Are you hearing a word I'm saying?

45:19.557 --> 45:20.888
[CHATTERING]

45:23.695 --> 45:25.094
Louis.

45:25.863 --> 45:28.696
Come on.
It's about time I met your family.

45:29.901 --> 45:32.529
[CHRIS TRAPPER'S "THIS TIME"
PLAYING IN DISTANCE]

45:33.237 --> 45:36.729
Listen, Jen,
maybe this isn't such a good idea.

45:37.709 --> 45:38.733
Grow up.

45:39.210 --> 45:40.677
Come on.

45:42.580 --> 45:43.842
-Come on.
-"Grow up."

45:45.683 --> 45:48.208
<i>[SINGING ON VIDEO]
The angel on the stairs</i>

45:48.386 --> 45:51.913
JEN: Are all Irish people this loud?
-Yeah.

45:52.090 --> 45:54.615
<i>Will tell you I was there</i>

45:57.195 --> 46:00.756
<i>Under the front porch light</i>

46:00.932 --> 46:03.867
<i>On a mystery night</i>

46:10.241 --> 46:14.940
<i>I been sitting
Watching life pass from the sidelines</i>

46:15.913 --> 46:16.902
MAN:
Hey, Louis.

46:17.081 --> 46:19.049
<i>Been waiting for a dream</i>

46:19.217 --> 46:22.914
<i>To seep in through my blinds</i>

46:24.489 --> 46:26.889
NICK:
Hey, Marshall, your brother's here.

46:27.291 --> 46:28.315
Louis.

46:31.028 --> 46:32.495
Hey, Nick.

46:32.897 --> 46:34.455
<i>Could I get you off my mind</i>

46:34.999 --> 46:38.696
JEN:
Oh, my God. Is that you?

46:38.870 --> 46:40.963
<i>This time?</i>

46:41.906 --> 46:44.340
When were you gonna tell me
you're in a band?

46:46.744 --> 46:50.145
I'm sure there's a lot of things
our Louis hasn't told you, darling.

46:50.314 --> 46:53.306
-Like who did you write the song for?
-I told you this is a mistake.

46:53.851 --> 46:56.444
That's it, go on. Walk out on us again.

46:59.422 --> 47:01.686
-Eh, Lou?
LOUIS: Say what you gotta say, Marshall.

47:01.858 --> 47:03.826
-Say what you have to say.
-No, go on.

47:03.994 --> 47:06.087
-Come on, say it.
MARSHALL: That the best you got?

47:06.263 --> 47:07.924
-Say it.
-That the best you got?

47:08.098 --> 47:10.328
-Come on. Hit me. Come on, hit me.
-Come on.

47:10.500 --> 47:12.661
Feel what? Come on. Hit me.

47:14.004 --> 47:15.301
I'm suffocating here.

47:16.072 --> 47:18.404
<i>The things I left behind</i>

47:22.112 --> 47:23.602
You all right, man?

47:25.682 --> 47:27.377
You all right, man?

47:28.051 --> 47:29.780
Welcome to the Connelly clan.

47:29.953 --> 47:31.750
[MARSHALL LAUGHS]

47:37.494 --> 47:39.121
Jennifer.

48:04.554 --> 48:07.489
You know, it was good
having the old Louis back in there...

48:08.024 --> 48:10.390
...even if it was only for a second.

48:12.362 --> 48:13.852
Louie...

48:14.297 --> 48:16.959
...aren't you supposed to be in the car
with the girl...

48:17.133 --> 48:19.294
...as she drives off into the sunset?

48:27.777 --> 48:30.337
You'll get your suit dirty
sitting there, man.

48:33.450 --> 48:36.886
[MARK MANCINA'S
"5-NOTE TRANSITION" PLAYING]

48:38.822 --> 48:41.052
[PHONE RINGING]

48:43.460 --> 48:44.449
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

48:44.628 --> 48:46.755
<i>WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
This is a message for Lyla Novacek.</i>

48:46.930 --> 48:49.057
<i>Please call Good Samaritan Hospital.</i>

48:49.232 --> 48:52.690
<i>I'm calling about your father,
Thomas Novacek.</i>

49:02.312 --> 49:04.644
THOMAS:
I wasn't sure you were going to come.

49:05.782 --> 49:08.216
My will is in the top drawer
of the desk in my study.

49:08.385 --> 49:10.910
Dad, stop, come on.

49:11.087 --> 49:13.248
THOMAS:
Lyla, please.

49:13.423 --> 49:15.220
There's more.

49:21.998 --> 49:27.732
All I ever wanted was for you
to have all that promise, all that life.

49:28.238 --> 49:30.172
But you were so young.

49:30.607 --> 49:32.700
We had so much work to do.

49:32.876 --> 49:36.141
-You weren't ready.
-That's plenty, Dad. Really.

49:36.947 --> 49:39.006
I mean, a baby.

49:39.182 --> 49:41.013
That baby, he could have hurt you.

49:41.184 --> 49:43.652
[MARK MANCINA'S
"HOSPITAL PT. 2" PLAYING]

49:44.120 --> 49:48.419
He could've hurt you, and I--
I wasn't gonna let that happen, Lyla.

49:53.896 --> 49:55.989
I made a choice for us.

49:59.835 --> 50:01.700
Oh, my God.

50:03.739 --> 50:04.967
<i>THOMAS:
A choice for us.</i>

50:06.942 --> 50:08.500
Wait....

50:13.649 --> 50:15.344
<i>THOMAS:
I'm sorry.</i>

50:20.222 --> 50:21.519
Where?

50:24.593 --> 50:26.424
Where is he?

50:27.229 --> 50:30.790
-I didn't mean--
-Where is he?

50:31.233 --> 50:32.461
I don't know.

50:34.503 --> 50:36.164
I don't.

50:38.207 --> 50:41.301
[PLAYING MICHAEL HEDGES'
"RITUAL DANCE"]

50:45.147 --> 50:47.809
<i>WALLACE: You gotta love music
more than you love food.</i>

50:48.751 --> 50:52.414
More than life. More than yourself.

50:58.827 --> 51:00.055
You feel it?

51:03.665 --> 51:04.689
Then show me.

51:05.434 --> 51:07.402
Play it for your parents.

51:56.952 --> 51:58.476
You're flying, kid.

51:58.654 --> 52:01.248
[CROWD CLAPPING]

52:08.530 --> 52:10.088
WALLACE:
Yeah!

52:10.265 --> 52:12.392
You know what I'm thinking?

52:13.268 --> 52:15.828
You're supposed to say,
"What are you thinking, Wizard?"

52:16.004 --> 52:18.302
"What are you thinking, Wizard?"

52:18.474 --> 52:20.908
I teach you everything I know for free.

52:21.076 --> 52:23.977
You get Roxanne.
You get my corner of the park.

52:24.413 --> 52:27.814
You get to keep half your tips.
We're like a team.

52:29.351 --> 52:31.319
There's something wrong
with that picture.

52:31.753 --> 52:32.811
What?

52:33.589 --> 52:36.921
I don't think performing in parks
and street corners is gonna be enough.

52:37.091 --> 52:38.319
It won't?

52:41.496 --> 52:44.829
Evan, we're gonna need
to get you a new name.

52:44.999 --> 52:46.762
Something with a little more pop.

52:47.201 --> 52:50.796
What do you wanna be in the world?
In the whole world, what do you wanna be?

52:50.972 --> 52:53.099
Close your eyes and think about that.

52:55.276 --> 52:56.766
Found.

53:02.016 --> 53:03.381
Doesn't have enough yin.

53:04.152 --> 53:06.279
-Little more yang, you know?
-Yeah.

53:06.454 --> 53:07.614
Yeah, let's....

53:07.788 --> 53:09.346
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

53:09.524 --> 53:13.483
Talk about wishful thinking. Look at that.

53:16.631 --> 53:18.690
What name stands out to you
on that, huh?

53:18.866 --> 53:19.890
Beach?

53:20.067 --> 53:22.501
It's a good name for a band,
but not for a performer.

53:22.670 --> 53:25.605
You can't say, "Please welcome Beach."
No, no.

53:25.773 --> 53:30.073
August Rush. August Rush.
Doesn't that warm you up a little bit?

53:30.511 --> 53:33.844
I can see it.
"Wizard Productions presents...

53:34.015 --> 53:36.882
...the number-one heat wave:

53:37.051 --> 53:40.509
August Rush!"

53:40.688 --> 53:43.248
-Yeah.
-Yeah. Me!

53:43.424 --> 53:46.086
-August, August, August.
-It gives me a rush.

53:46.260 --> 53:49.559
That gives me chills. The hair
on the back of my neck's standing up.

53:49.730 --> 53:51.197
-Really?
-Yeah, look at that.

53:51.365 --> 53:52.798
Quick, check it out. Yeah.

53:52.967 --> 53:56.596
-I'm flying! I'm flying!
-Yeah. August! August Rush.

53:56.771 --> 53:59.069
-August.
-August Rush. August Rush.

53:59.240 --> 54:00.264
That's you.

54:00.641 --> 54:03.041
<i>WALLACE: August. August.
AUGUST: August Rush, August Rush.</i>

54:05.079 --> 54:07.741
[LUCAS REYNOLDS'
"SOMETHING INSIDE" PLAYING]

54:47.421 --> 54:48.547
[THUNDER CRASHES]

54:48.723 --> 54:51.021
<i>LIZZY: New York, Lyla?
What are you doing in New York?</i>

54:51.192 --> 54:53.956
Lizzy, I mean,
I've always felt that he was alive.

54:54.128 --> 54:59.430
I'd see kids that would be his age
and I'd imagine what he'd look like.

54:59.600 --> 55:02.364
<i>-Big blue eyes like his dad and--
-Oh, my God, Lyla.</i>

55:02.536 --> 55:06.973
Lizzy, I used to lie in bed at night
and I swear I could hear him.

55:07.141 --> 55:10.110
<i>-I swear I could hear him.
-Lyla, calm down.</i>

55:10.278 --> 55:13.941
Calm down? How can I be calm?
How can I be calm?

55:14.115 --> 55:17.380
I've been calm for over 10 years
and look where it's gotten me.

55:17.551 --> 55:20.042
<i>Lyla, you're losing it.</i>

55:20.288 --> 55:23.519
You're right. And maybe it's about time.

55:23.691 --> 55:25.385
<i>Don't do anything crazy, okay?</i>

55:25.558 --> 55:29.892
<i>We're on our honeymoon, but we're leaving.
We'll get there as soon as we can, okay?</i>

55:49.316 --> 55:52.183
Okay, Jack, he's worth three times
what you're offering him.

55:52.352 --> 55:54.149
-Wallace--
-You heard him in the park!

55:54.321 --> 55:55.583
You're a pain in the ass.

55:55.755 --> 55:59.156
-Two-fifty if he can play for two hours.
-No, five or he walks.

55:59.326 --> 56:04.127
-Five hundred? I'll give him 250--
-Five hundred or he walks, all right?

56:04.297 --> 56:05.286
JACK:
He walks?

56:05.465 --> 56:07.695
WALLACE:
We have lightning in a bottle, Jack.

56:07.867 --> 56:10.392
No, there's no parents. I'm his guardian.

56:10.570 --> 56:13.767
No, I'm his representation,
that's why I'm making the deal.

56:13.940 --> 56:15.669
WOMAN:
May I help you?

56:16.076 --> 56:18.306
-I'm trying to find my son.
WOMAN: Hold on a second.

56:19.045 --> 56:20.706
Name?

56:26.019 --> 56:28.010
GIRL 1:
Mommy.

56:28.988 --> 56:31.923
[MARK MANCINA'S
"PLAYGROUND" PLAYING]

56:33.827 --> 56:35.761
Mommy.

56:38.598 --> 56:40.065
I don't know.

56:41.501 --> 56:44.061
GIRL 2: Mom.
GIRL 3: Mommy.

56:54.114 --> 56:56.241
Mommy, look at me.

56:56.416 --> 56:58.907
I'm sorry, ma'am, we're closing.

57:00.253 --> 57:04.053
Please, I just-- I wanna know his name.

57:04.824 --> 57:10.023
To even consider re-establishing contact
with a child, there is a detailed process.

57:10.196 --> 57:14.860
I don't care about your process! Okay?

57:31.050 --> 57:35.544
WOMAN: Ma'am, we're closed.
Come back tomorrow.

57:39.092 --> 57:40.821
<i>LOUIS:
Lyla.</i>

57:41.861 --> 57:43.328
<i>Novacek.</i>

57:46.166 --> 57:48.999
<i>LYLA [ON RECORDING]: Hi, this is Lyla--
LIZZY [ON RECORDING]: And Lizzy.</i>

57:49.169 --> 57:51.797
<i>LYLA & LIZZY: And we're not here
right now, so leave a message.</i>

57:51.971 --> 57:53.563
[MACHINE BEEPS]

58:12.192 --> 58:13.716
WALLACE:
Arthur!

58:14.593 --> 58:16.823
What'd I tell you
about talking to strangers?

58:16.995 --> 58:20.453
-Yeah, what's your name?
-My name is Mr. Jeffries, and yours?

58:20.966 --> 58:23.196
Arthur. We ain't strangers now.

58:23.735 --> 58:27.933
Look, Mr. Wallace,
I'm here making my normal rounds.

58:28.106 --> 58:29.664
I'm trying to find these kids.

58:29.842 --> 58:33.073
This girl, her name is Geralda.
She should be about 14 now.

58:33.245 --> 58:34.678
Don't know her, Mr. Jeffries.

58:34.847 --> 58:37.873
Okay, well, maybe you can help me
with this young man.

58:38.050 --> 58:41.952
Little boy that came up missing recently
and his name is Evan Taylor.

58:42.788 --> 58:44.949
He's about 12.

58:47.092 --> 58:50.721
And what if I find this Evan
and I turn him over to you?

58:51.296 --> 58:55.198
What then? You don't care about a kid
after he's in the system.

58:55.367 --> 58:58.962
-It's not like that--
-Oh, I know exactly what it's like.

58:59.137 --> 59:03.130
You don't follow up.
And you throw him from place to place.

59:03.308 --> 59:06.903
Eventually, you end up in a place
where they kick the crap out of you.

59:07.346 --> 59:11.976
Go to bed at night
and he tries to close his eyes, ears.

59:12.150 --> 59:13.845
Shut out the world.

59:14.019 --> 59:17.546
What happens to that kid?
What do you think he hears?

59:18.156 --> 59:19.851
What do you think he hears?

59:21.593 --> 59:23.720
-Nothing.
-Nothing. Nothing at all.

59:27.466 --> 59:28.592
Are you all right?

59:29.201 --> 59:30.759
-Yeah, I'm cool.
-He's good.

59:39.678 --> 59:41.737
<i>MAN:
Fourteenth Precinct, Sergeant O'Malley.</i>

59:42.548 --> 59:45.108
WALLACE:
No. That doesn't cut it.

59:45.284 --> 59:47.514
[PLAYING MARK MANCINA'S
"WIND UP"]

59:47.686 --> 59:50.746
No! Oh, is that final?

59:50.923 --> 59:54.324
Okay, well, here's my final offer:
we're history!

59:55.360 --> 59:57.487
-Deal's off.
-But I wanna play.

59:57.663 --> 01:00:00.632
You play when I say play.
You breathe when I say breathe.

01:00:00.799 --> 01:00:03.427
-You got that, boy?
-But I have to play.

01:00:03.602 --> 01:00:05.729
Wizard, I need them to hear.

01:00:05.904 --> 01:00:10.864
You forget about your parents!
They were pretty quick to forget about you.

01:00:11.944 --> 01:00:14.913
[MARK MANCINA'S
"AGAINST THE GATE" PLAYING]

01:00:16.715 --> 01:00:19.149
You don't know how it could be for you.

01:00:19.318 --> 01:00:22.151
You do not know how precious
your gift is.

01:00:22.321 --> 01:00:25.051
You're just a kid, you don't know.

01:00:29.795 --> 01:00:32.025
I do, August.

01:00:43.408 --> 01:00:45.638
[SIRENS WAILING]

01:00:46.979 --> 01:00:49.379
<i>BOY: Wizard. Wizard.
WALLACE: Shh! Talk to me. What happened?</i>

01:00:49.548 --> 01:00:52.984
-It's Arthur. The cops chased him here.
-Okay, split up. You know the drill.

01:00:53.151 --> 01:00:55.642
-We gotta help Arty.
-Forget Arty. Arty's on his own.

01:00:55.821 --> 01:00:57.812
-That's the book.
-No.

01:00:57.990 --> 01:01:00.288
WALLACE: August!
COP 1: Grab him. Grab him. There he goes.

01:01:01.293 --> 01:01:02.783
COP 2:
He went outside over there.

01:01:02.961 --> 01:01:05.588
[MARK MANCINA'S
"THE RAID" PLAYING]

01:01:15.940 --> 01:01:19.273
Up there. You see him?
See him? Look, over there.

01:01:19.443 --> 01:01:21.274
COP 2: Hey, kid, don't move.
-Hey, you!

01:01:21.445 --> 01:01:24.005
Cops. Cops.

01:01:24.649 --> 01:01:26.708
Cops. Over here.

01:01:29.353 --> 01:01:32.083
COP 2: Grab that kid over there.
Grab him, grab him.

01:01:38.763 --> 01:01:40.958
Listen, you can't let the cops catch you.

01:01:41.132 --> 01:01:43.532
If they do,
you don't tell them your real name...

01:01:43.701 --> 01:01:47.137
...because they'll send you right back
where you came from, you got that?

01:01:48.005 --> 01:01:49.370
I don't wanna lose you...

01:01:49.540 --> 01:01:51.906
...but if we get separated,
we meet at the arch.

01:01:53.878 --> 01:01:55.675
Do not tell them your name.

01:01:55.846 --> 01:02:00.909
Hey, when I say run, you run, okay?

01:02:07.725 --> 01:02:08.919
COP 1:
Let me see your hands.

01:02:09.093 --> 01:02:10.685
[SCREAMS]

01:02:11.929 --> 01:02:16.161
WALLACE: Run, August. Run, August. Run!
COP 2: Hey, kid.

01:02:26.977 --> 01:02:28.001
Hey, kid, stop.

01:02:34.351 --> 01:02:35.409
Open the door.

01:02:35.586 --> 01:02:36.575
[BUZZES]

01:02:48.032 --> 01:02:50.865
[JAMAL JOSEPH'S "HARLEM STREETZ"
PLAYING ON CAR STEREO IN DISTANCE]

01:03:07.451 --> 01:03:12.013
<i>MAN [SINGING]: How I don't need that man
But they don't understand</i>

01:03:12.189 --> 01:03:14.714
<i>There's far too many pressures in reality</i>

01:03:15.860 --> 01:03:18.954
<i>Dealing with the pain of stress and poverty</i>

01:03:19.130 --> 01:03:25.694
<i>And I gotta be myself because
There's nobody else for me, no</i>

01:03:25.870 --> 01:03:27.599
<i>Hang in there with me</i>

01:03:27.772 --> 01:03:30.639
<i>Sometimes it takes a different kind of love
To raise a child</i>

01:03:30.808 --> 01:03:32.901
<i>-So don't give up
-So don't give up</i>

01:03:33.077 --> 01:03:34.339
<i>When pressures come down</i>

01:03:34.512 --> 01:03:37.845
<i>Sometimes it takes a different kind of dream
To make you smile</i>

01:03:38.015 --> 01:03:39.482
<i>-So raise it up
-So raise</i>

01:03:39.650 --> 01:03:41.277
<i>Hang in there with me</i>

01:03:41.452 --> 01:03:44.512
<i>Sometimes we need another helping hand
To show the way</i>

01:03:44.688 --> 01:03:46.417
<i>-So don't give up
-So don't give up</i>

01:03:46.590 --> 01:03:48.148
<i>When pressures come down</i>

01:03:48.325 --> 01:03:51.226
<i>Sometimes it seems impossible
And that's why we pray</i>

01:03:51.395 --> 01:03:53.362
<i>-So raise it up
-We pray</i>

01:03:53.530 --> 01:03:56.658
<i>Seems to be nothing left for me</i>

01:03:56.833 --> 01:03:59.427
<i>Mama's gone, Daddy didn't wanna be</i>

01:04:00.370 --> 01:04:04.033
<i>Now I'm all by myself
Wondering where is love</i>

01:04:04.207 --> 01:04:06.198
<i>Or should I just give up, you know</i>

01:04:06.376 --> 01:04:10.312
<i>Life falls down on me
Cuts into my soul</i>

01:04:10.480 --> 01:04:13.938
<i>But I know I got the strength
To make it through it all</i>

01:04:14.117 --> 01:04:17.609
<i>Cause I'm still standing tall
Breaking through these walls</i>

01:04:17.787 --> 01:04:21.188
<i>I'm gonna give my all, hey</i>

01:04:21.357 --> 01:04:24.053
<i>I'm feeling like a motherless child</i>

01:04:24.394 --> 01:04:26.919
<i>Pain cuts into my soul</i>

01:04:27.630 --> 01:04:28.961
<i>It's beaten me down</i>

01:04:29.132 --> 01:04:33.694
<i>Can't find a smile
On the face of a motherless child</i>

01:04:33.870 --> 01:04:36.964
<i>Gonna break down these walls
Gonna give my all</i>

01:04:37.140 --> 01:04:41.440
<i>You know
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah</i>

01:04:41.611 --> 01:04:43.135
<i>Hang in there with me</i>

01:04:43.313 --> 01:04:46.339
<i>Sometimes it takes a different kind of love
To raise a child</i>

01:04:46.516 --> 01:04:48.313
<i>-So don't give up
-So don't give up</i>

01:04:48.484 --> 01:04:49.678
<i>When pressures come down</i>

01:04:49.853 --> 01:04:53.345
<i>Sometimes it takes a different kind of dream
To make you smile</i>

01:04:53.523 --> 01:04:55.081
<i>-So raise it up
-So raise it up</i>

01:04:55.258 --> 01:04:57.249
<i>-Hang in there with me
-Raise it up</i>

01:04:57.427 --> 01:05:00.260
<i>Sometimes it takes another's helping hand
To show you the way</i>

01:05:00.430 --> 01:05:01.419
<i>So don't give up</i>

01:05:01.598 --> 01:05:03.691
<i>-Oh, no, yeah
-When pressures come down</i>

01:05:03.867 --> 01:05:06.700
<i>Sometimes it seems impossible
That's why we pray</i>

01:05:06.870 --> 01:05:07.859
<i>So raise it up</i>

01:05:15.245 --> 01:05:17.338
LYLA: Hi.
-Hi.

01:05:17.847 --> 01:05:22.250
I know how this looks, you know.
I'm not crazy.

01:05:22.418 --> 01:05:25.512
Nobody thinks you're crazy.
What's your name?

01:05:25.688 --> 01:05:27.918
Lyla Novacek.

01:05:28.091 --> 01:05:30.059
Well, it's like
the woman explained to you.

01:05:30.226 --> 01:05:32.786
-You fill out a couple forms--
-Six months, they said.

01:05:32.962 --> 01:05:36.329
I don't have six months for forms.

01:05:36.499 --> 01:05:38.592
Then I can't help you, then.

01:05:39.202 --> 01:05:42.262
Explain something to me now. Why now?

01:05:43.039 --> 01:05:46.736
Why not before? Why is it so important
that you want him now?

01:05:47.944 --> 01:05:50.139
I've always wanted him.

01:05:52.515 --> 01:05:56.417
I've waited 11 years, two months,
and 15 days...

01:05:57.353 --> 01:05:59.981
...to find out that he's alive.

01:06:03.059 --> 01:06:04.890
I've been counting.

01:06:06.529 --> 01:06:08.861
[LUCAS REYNOLDS'
"SOMETHING INSIDE" PLAYING]

01:06:16.906 --> 01:06:19.033
[PHONE DIALING]

01:06:21.744 --> 01:06:24.178
<i>- [ON RECORDING] Hi, this is Lyla--
-And Lizzy.</i>

01:06:24.347 --> 01:06:26.815
<i>And we're not here right now,
so leave a message.</i>

01:06:26.983 --> 01:06:28.917
[MACHINE BEEPS]

01:06:32.255 --> 01:06:34.849
<i>MAN [SINGING]:
When the one thing you're looking for</i>

01:06:35.024 --> 01:06:36.184
[PHONE DIALING]

01:06:36.359 --> 01:06:38.884
<i>Is nowhere to be found</i>

01:06:41.998 --> 01:06:45.125
<i>And you're back-stepping
All of your moves</i>

01:06:45.300 --> 01:06:47.325
<i>Trying to figure it out</i>

01:06:47.502 --> 01:06:48.764
MAN:
What are you waiting for?

01:06:48.937 --> 01:06:51.667
You see, I know this girl
that lives across the street.

01:06:51.840 --> 01:06:52.864
Lyla Novacek.

01:06:53.041 --> 01:06:55.134
I've been standing outside here waiting.

01:06:55.310 --> 01:06:56.675
I wrote her a song.

01:06:56.845 --> 01:07:00.303
WOMAN: Oh, the musician.
She keeps me up half the night.

01:07:00.482 --> 01:07:04.680
Well, I haven't seen her in a few days.
She's off on her honeymoon.

01:07:07.089 --> 01:07:08.818
Thanks.

01:07:08.991 --> 01:07:14.361
<i>MAN [SINGING]: And you wanna give out
You wanna give in</i>

01:07:14.529 --> 01:07:19.330
<i>Your head's wrapped around
What's around the next bend</i>

01:07:19.801 --> 01:07:23.237
<i>You wish you could find
Something warm</i>

01:07:23.405 --> 01:07:26.897
<i>'Cause you're shivering cold</i>

01:07:32.414 --> 01:07:37.545
<i>It's the first thing you see
As you open your eyes</i>

01:07:37.719 --> 01:07:42.452
<i>The last thing you say
As you're saying goodbye</i>

01:07:42.624 --> 01:07:48.893
<i>But something inside you
Is crying and driving you on</i>

01:07:49.631 --> 01:07:51.758
RICHARD:
And this isn't your signature?

01:07:53.201 --> 01:07:58.070
You do realize that he's probably
already been placed with a family, correct?

01:07:58.240 --> 01:08:00.674
Do you have children, Mr. Jeffries?

01:08:08.483 --> 01:08:10.849
Yeah, I did.

01:08:12.721 --> 01:08:14.245
Then you know.

01:08:22.096 --> 01:08:23.359
What's his birthday?

01:08:23.999 --> 01:08:26.365
December 17th, 1995.

01:08:28.069 --> 01:08:29.229
Yeah, I know.

01:08:41.850 --> 01:08:44.011
Excuse me a minute.

01:09:02.203 --> 01:09:04.899
[MARK MANCINA'S
"PHOTO OF EVAN" PLAYING]

01:09:12.247 --> 01:09:13.942
This is him.

01:09:18.620 --> 01:09:20.144
Yeah.

01:09:21.689 --> 01:09:24.591
[BELLS TOLLING]

01:09:38.671 --> 01:09:40.799
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

01:09:40.975 --> 01:09:43.273
[MARK MANCINA'S "PIANO LESSON"
PLAYING ON PIANO]

01:09:59.894 --> 01:10:01.953
You the one slept under my bed?

01:10:07.268 --> 01:10:08.326
Do you live here?

01:10:08.936 --> 01:10:11.131
Me and my grandma do,
till our boat comes in.

01:10:14.341 --> 01:10:15.569
Do you like music?

01:10:17.111 --> 01:10:18.169
More than food.

01:10:21.348 --> 01:10:23.077
Do you know your notes?

01:10:24.418 --> 01:10:26.318
I've never seen them like that before.

01:10:26.487 --> 01:10:28.079
See here:

01:10:28.923 --> 01:10:33.826
"Every Good Boy Does Fine"
on the lines.

01:10:33.994 --> 01:10:39.398
And "F, A, C, E" in between.

01:10:39.567 --> 01:10:43.094
And "Great Big Dogs Fight Animals."

01:10:43.270 --> 01:10:48.230
And "All Cars Eat Gas." Get it?

01:10:49.176 --> 01:10:50.666
You're like an angel.

01:10:51.512 --> 01:10:53.241
Okay. I gotta go.

01:10:53.714 --> 01:10:55.409
Gotta go to school.

01:11:00.721 --> 01:11:02.450
Can I borrow this?

01:11:03.190 --> 01:11:04.851
Later.

01:11:11.832 --> 01:11:14.164
[THUDS]

01:11:26.747 --> 01:11:29.443
[PLAYING MARK MANCINA'S
"BASKETBALL"]

01:12:32.378 --> 01:12:34.039
Holy....

01:12:37.317 --> 01:12:39.512
Reverend J.!

01:13:05.611 --> 01:13:07.636
[ORGAN SOUNDS]

01:13:07.814 --> 01:13:10.647
You're not gonna believe this,
Reverend J. Come quick.

01:13:10.817 --> 01:13:13.718
-Whoa. Slow down, Hope.
-You've gotta see what's happened.

01:13:13.886 --> 01:13:17.879
[PLAYING MARK MANCINA'S
"3 NOTE THEME"]

01:13:34.707 --> 01:13:37.335
Remember in Music Appreciation
we had a class on Mozart?

01:13:37.510 --> 01:13:38.534
Yes.

01:13:38.711 --> 01:13:40.736
Remember you said
he was like a musical pod?

01:13:40.913 --> 01:13:42.847
-Prodigy.
-Exactly.

01:13:43.015 --> 01:13:45.916
Well, I have one of those,
and he's living under my bed.

01:13:54.193 --> 01:13:57.822
So I showed him the scales
and when I came home, he was....

01:14:30.530 --> 01:14:33.966
<i>LYLA:
Mr. Jeffries, hi, it's Lyla Novacek again.</i>

01:14:34.133 --> 01:14:36.966
<i>I was just checking in.</i>

01:14:39.439 --> 01:14:40.838
<i>Right, I understand.</i>

01:14:41.007 --> 01:14:44.135
<i>You know,
if there's any more information or--</i>

01:14:44.310 --> 01:14:46.141
<i>Yeah, just call.</i>

01:14:59.859 --> 01:15:01.520
I'll take it.

01:15:01.694 --> 01:15:04.288
WOMAN:
How long do you think you'll be staying?

01:15:05.331 --> 01:15:07.822
<i>LYLA:
As long as it takes.</i>

01:15:28.820 --> 01:15:30.378
Sorry.

01:15:30.555 --> 01:15:33.251
<i>LYLA:
I don't know, Lizzy, it's like...</i>

01:15:33.625 --> 01:15:35.456
<i>...I just woke up...</i>

01:15:35.627 --> 01:15:37.959
<i>...and I should start playing again.</i>

01:15:38.129 --> 01:15:40.029
<i>I should play.</i>

01:15:40.499 --> 01:15:43.832
<i>I know it sounds crazy,
but maybe he'll hear me.</i>

01:15:59.951 --> 01:16:02.818
<i>LOUIS:
Hey, Marshall. It's me.</i>

01:16:04.422 --> 01:16:06.287
<i>I'm in New York.</i>

01:16:07.993 --> 01:16:10.518
<i>Is the band still minus
one mad Connelly brother?</i>

01:16:11.563 --> 01:16:14.327
<i>Having you guys here,
it'd be great, you know?</i>

01:16:15.734 --> 01:16:17.099
<i>Just an idea.</i>

01:16:17.269 --> 01:16:20.067
Hey, Frank. It's Louis.

01:16:20.438 --> 01:16:22.269
Louis Connelly.

01:16:22.440 --> 01:16:23.873
And?

01:16:24.042 --> 01:16:26.533
I played here with me band
a couple of years ago.

01:16:26.711 --> 01:16:28.702
Well, about 10 years ago.

01:16:31.283 --> 01:16:33.649
Hey, hey, listen, Frank.

01:16:34.185 --> 01:16:37.677
I'm gonna play you one song, all right?
Just one song.

01:16:37.856 --> 01:16:41.485
And if you don't like it,
you can throw me out.

01:16:43.061 --> 01:16:45.894
[MARK MANCINA'S
"AUGUST TO JUILLIARD" PLAYING]

01:16:58.343 --> 01:17:00.641
<i>WOMAN:
You brought us a prodigy, Reverend.</i>

01:17:00.812 --> 01:17:03.508
-He is a mystery.
MAN: Here in the "Well-Tempered Clavier"....

01:17:03.682 --> 01:17:06.378
Dean, I thought he was an angel.

01:17:07.285 --> 01:17:10.550
There's no record of
an August Rush anywhere.

01:17:10.722 --> 01:17:15.159
MAN: It's about foundation,
starting with a very simple, orderly chord.

01:17:15.327 --> 01:17:18.057
<i>LOUIS [SINGING]:
As you open your eyes</i>

01:17:18.229 --> 01:17:22.859
<i>The last thing you say
As you're saying goodbye</i>

01:17:23.034 --> 01:17:25.400
<i>But something inside you</i>

01:17:25.570 --> 01:17:29.904
<i>Is crying and driving you on</i>

01:17:30.442 --> 01:17:33.309
[CELLO PLAYING DAVE METZGER'S
"CELLO CONCERTO IN E MINOR"]

01:17:39.150 --> 01:17:41.744
LIZZY:
Lyla, just relax.

01:17:41.920 --> 01:17:44.252
LYLA: This piece.
LIZZY: You're pushing yourself too hard.

01:17:44.422 --> 01:17:46.686
I don't know if I can do this.

01:17:46.858 --> 01:17:49.383
LIZZY:
You're playing with the Philharmonic.

01:17:49.561 --> 01:17:51.495
That's great.

01:17:53.398 --> 01:17:55.696
Okay, let's keep going.

01:18:03.007 --> 01:18:06.670
MAN: Start with a C-major chord,
then a modulation to G.

01:18:06.844 --> 01:18:09.836
Once we get to G,
we go back to C, very simple.

01:18:10.014 --> 01:18:12.778
And we have C, G, C.

01:18:20.491 --> 01:18:22.391
<i>At the very beginning, C-major chord.</i>

01:18:22.559 --> 01:18:27.155
<i>We have this chaotic evolution
into a remote G-major.</i>

01:18:30.501 --> 01:18:32.492
C-major chord, then move into a G.

01:18:41.311 --> 01:18:43.779
What's this, August?

01:18:44.081 --> 01:18:46.276
The diminished fifth, sir.

01:18:46.650 --> 01:18:48.083
Key change here.

01:18:48.252 --> 01:18:51.016
And then the rise
with those round horns...

01:18:51.188 --> 01:18:55.249
...the oboes,
into the allegro staccato strings.

01:18:56.660 --> 01:18:58.560
[KNOCKING]

01:19:00.864 --> 01:19:03.389
Ah. Mr. Rush.

01:19:06.870 --> 01:19:10.237
-I'm sorry.
-Why are you apologizing, August?

01:19:11.442 --> 01:19:12.909
Sometimes I don't listen well...

01:19:13.077 --> 01:19:15.545
...and I don't do the homework
like I'm supposed to.

01:19:15.713 --> 01:19:18.011
Well, I'm sure you'll do better
in the future.

01:19:29.193 --> 01:19:32.185
The New York Philharmonic Orchestra
is having a concert.

01:19:32.830 --> 01:19:36.960
In the history of this school we have never
performed the work of a first-year student...

01:19:37.134 --> 01:19:40.035
...and certainly no one of your age.

01:19:40.204 --> 01:19:44.300
But now, we've asked them
if they could perform your rhapsody.

01:19:44.475 --> 01:19:46.033
Would you like that?

01:19:46.944 --> 01:19:49.412
Well, good. Good.

01:19:49.580 --> 01:19:51.241
How many people will hear it?

01:19:54.017 --> 01:19:57.783
Well, it would be performed in Central Park,
on the Great Lawn.

01:19:57.955 --> 01:19:58.979
A hundred?

01:20:00.157 --> 01:20:02.057
Much more. Thousands.

01:20:02.893 --> 01:20:07.455
Okay. Because I need to play it
to a lot of people. Lots and lots.

01:20:07.631 --> 01:20:08.893
[PEOPLE CHUCKLING]

01:20:09.066 --> 01:20:10.761
We'll see what we can do to help.

01:20:13.270 --> 01:20:19.300
DEAN: August, three artists will be
performing, and you will be featured last.

01:20:19.910 --> 01:20:22.276
[MARK MANCINA'S
"JUILLIARD MONTAGE" PLAYING]

01:20:30.521 --> 01:20:32.318
<i>How do you do it?</i>

01:20:32.723 --> 01:20:36.090
How does the music come to you?

01:20:38.228 --> 01:20:39.991
<i>AUGUST:
I just hear it.</i>

01:20:43.934 --> 01:20:45.765
Sometimes I wake up and it's there...

01:20:45.936 --> 01:20:48.769
...or I hear it
when I'm walking down the street.

01:20:50.140 --> 01:20:54.769
[MARK MANCINA'S
"JUILLIARD MONTAGE" PLAYING]

01:20:55.878 --> 01:20:58.438
<i>It's like someone's calling out to me.</i>

01:20:59.348 --> 01:21:02.010
Writing it all down
is like I'm calling back to them.

01:21:02.185 --> 01:21:03.447
Who?

01:21:04.954 --> 01:21:07.149
The ones who gave me the music.

01:21:14.497 --> 01:21:16.431
MARSHALL:
You sure you're ready for this, Louis?

01:21:16.599 --> 01:21:17.896
Are you?

01:21:44.727 --> 01:21:48.060
[ORCHESTRA PLAYING MARK MANCINA'S
"RHAPSODY REHEARSAL"]

01:22:18.194 --> 01:22:19.889
Bravo, August!

01:22:22.431 --> 01:22:23.898
Good one!

01:22:27.336 --> 01:22:31.534
August, boy, you're a hard guy to find.

01:22:33.876 --> 01:22:35.366
Been looking everywhere for you.

01:22:35.544 --> 01:22:38.980
Excuse me.
You're interrupting a rehearsal here.

01:22:39.148 --> 01:22:41.708
WALLACE: Yeah, rehearsal, right.
MAN: And you are...?

01:22:41.884 --> 01:22:43.476
Come here to me, son.

01:22:53.262 --> 01:22:54.820
Come here.

01:22:57.934 --> 01:22:59.799
What'd they do to you?

01:23:01.404 --> 01:23:02.894
Nothing.

01:23:05.408 --> 01:23:07.399
These people can steal your soul.

01:23:08.244 --> 01:23:10.474
Sir, whomever you are,
you don't have the right.

01:23:10.646 --> 01:23:13.581
I'm his father, all right?
I have every right.

01:23:17.687 --> 01:23:20.451
I'll take you home now. Come on.

01:23:21.057 --> 01:23:24.151
But I have a concert. I like it here.

01:23:24.327 --> 01:23:26.852
-He's a remarkable boy--
WALLACE: You don't think I know that?

01:23:27.029 --> 01:23:30.795
What'd you do, you just snatched him up
off the street? That gives you the right?

01:23:31.400 --> 01:23:33.664
Wait a moment,
we've been teaching him here.

01:23:33.836 --> 01:23:35.064
What are you gonna do?

01:23:35.237 --> 01:23:38.934
Fill his head with classical theory
and rules?

01:23:39.108 --> 01:23:42.076
You can't learn music from books.

01:23:42.243 --> 01:23:43.801
It's out there.

01:23:45.213 --> 01:23:47.579
You teach him? Ha!

01:23:48.016 --> 01:23:49.483
He teaches you.

01:23:49.651 --> 01:23:51.380
You learn from him.

01:23:51.553 --> 01:23:54.044
We are.
I assure you, Mr. Rush, every day.

01:23:55.190 --> 01:23:56.953
You should be with family. Come on.

01:24:00.362 --> 01:24:01.954
Mr. Rush, please.

01:24:02.130 --> 01:24:06.191
Do you have any idea of the importance
of the concert tomorrow night, for August?

01:24:07.002 --> 01:24:08.526
August. Wait, listen.

01:24:09.004 --> 01:24:11.871
You gotta tell me right now,
is this man really your father?

01:24:16.344 --> 01:24:18.175
You can tell me the truth.

01:24:19.347 --> 01:24:21.577
WALLACE:
I know your real name.

01:24:22.751 --> 01:24:24.150
Evan.

01:24:24.753 --> 01:24:26.653
MAN:
August.

01:24:26.821 --> 01:24:28.254
Evan.

01:24:30.658 --> 01:24:32.489
Is he your father?

01:24:32.660 --> 01:24:35.857
[MARK MANCINA'S
"WIZARD RETURNS" PLAYING]

01:24:36.998 --> 01:24:39.193
He taught me everything I know.

01:24:49.677 --> 01:24:51.611
[STRUMS GUITAR]

01:24:51.780 --> 01:24:53.441
ARTHUR:
And we are back, we are back.

01:24:57.285 --> 01:24:59.617
Don't make it harder for yourself, Aug.

01:24:59.788 --> 01:25:02.018
Wizard's not so bad.

01:25:03.291 --> 01:25:05.725
You saw the kid, right?
He's a freak of nature. Yeah.

01:25:05.894 --> 01:25:09.625
Here's the deal. Thousand a night, two
weeks minimum, three cities guaranteed.

01:25:09.798 --> 01:25:12.858
Then we ship him out to your partner
on the West Coast. No.

01:25:13.034 --> 01:25:14.899
ARTHUR:
He just ain't feeling well.

01:25:15.904 --> 01:25:19.203
He said you the only one
who gonna make him feel better.

01:25:26.314 --> 01:25:29.215
Competition. All right, I'll be back.
You do what you do.

01:25:33.121 --> 01:25:35.055
Yo, yo.

01:25:40.895 --> 01:25:43.557
I'm his representation.
That's why I'm making the deal.

01:25:44.399 --> 01:25:46.833
Come on. No, there's no parents.

01:26:17.098 --> 01:26:18.656
Great sounds, kid.

01:26:21.436 --> 01:26:23.028
Gibson J-200?

01:26:24.572 --> 01:26:26.039
It's beautiful.

01:26:26.641 --> 01:26:27.938
Can I see her?

01:26:31.378 --> 01:26:34.347
Hey. It's okay.

01:26:34.815 --> 01:26:36.874
I'm a musician too.

01:26:42.055 --> 01:26:43.579
Yeah.

01:26:47.661 --> 01:26:49.356
Oh, yeah.

01:26:54.635 --> 01:26:57.900
[PLAYING HEITOR PERIERA'S
"DUELING GUITARS"]

01:27:02.976 --> 01:27:04.307
Nice action.

01:27:05.345 --> 01:27:06.676
You're pretty good.

01:27:07.881 --> 01:27:09.508
Thanks.

01:27:10.450 --> 01:27:12.441
See what you can do with mine.

01:29:06.933 --> 01:29:08.332
How long you been playing?

01:29:08.769 --> 01:29:10.168
Six months.

01:29:10.804 --> 01:29:12.601
Six months?

01:29:12.773 --> 01:29:15.264
How'd you learn how to play like that
in six months?

01:29:15.442 --> 01:29:16.500
Juilliard.

01:29:18.145 --> 01:29:19.305
Juilliard?

01:29:19.812 --> 01:29:21.040
Yes, sir.

01:29:21.213 --> 01:29:23.181
I have my own concert tonight.

01:29:24.183 --> 01:29:25.844
Do you reckon I should believe you?

01:29:26.952 --> 01:29:29.614
Yeah. But I can't go.

01:29:30.056 --> 01:29:31.284
Why's that?

01:29:32.024 --> 01:29:34.390
It's kind of a long story.

01:29:36.729 --> 01:29:41.257
Well, if I went to Juilliard
and I had a concert tonight...

01:29:41.434 --> 01:29:43.334
...I wouldn't miss it for the world.

01:29:44.637 --> 01:29:46.070
Yeah.

01:29:51.243 --> 01:29:53.803
But what if something bad
would happen if you did it?

01:29:55.481 --> 01:29:57.676
You never quit on your music.

01:29:58.451 --> 01:30:00.544
No matter what happens.

01:30:01.153 --> 01:30:04.850
Because anytime
something bad happens to you...

01:30:05.257 --> 01:30:08.556
...it's the one place you can escape to
and just, psh, let it go.

01:30:10.696 --> 01:30:12.789
I learned that the hard way.

01:30:14.433 --> 01:30:16.333
And anyway, look at me.

01:30:17.370 --> 01:30:19.702
Nothing bad's gonna happen.

01:30:20.406 --> 01:30:22.533
You gotta have a little faith.

01:30:33.185 --> 01:30:34.413
I'm Louis.

01:30:35.488 --> 01:30:37.888
Ev-- August.

01:30:38.057 --> 01:30:39.718
August Rush.

01:30:39.892 --> 01:30:41.951
August Rush.

01:30:43.362 --> 01:30:45.694
-Cool name.
WALLACE: August!

01:30:47.032 --> 01:30:48.556
Come on!

01:30:51.637 --> 01:30:53.434
I gotta go, August.

01:30:59.745 --> 01:31:01.235
Bye.

01:31:02.014 --> 01:31:03.481
Yeah.

01:31:05.317 --> 01:31:06.807
Bye.

01:31:16.495 --> 01:31:17.894
Bye.

01:31:36.348 --> 01:31:39.078
Yes, I made him memorize our number.

01:31:41.654 --> 01:31:45.090
I understand. Your department's
doing everything they can.

01:32:04.076 --> 01:32:06.636
Do you think anything bad
happened to him?

01:32:07.746 --> 01:32:09.008
I'm sure he's fine.

01:32:10.081 --> 01:32:12.641
I prayed for him. Did you?

01:32:13.418 --> 01:32:15.079
Yeah.

01:32:16.254 --> 01:32:19.621
Well, if his father loves him like he should...

01:32:19.791 --> 01:32:22.954
...then he'll do what's best for his son.

01:32:24.863 --> 01:32:26.490
You believe that, don't you?

01:32:27.465 --> 01:32:30.263
-Yeah.
-Good.

01:32:30.568 --> 01:32:32.433
Now go get ready.

01:32:32.837 --> 01:32:38.104
[MARK MANCINA'S
"ARPEGGIO THEME" PLAYING]

01:32:43.414 --> 01:32:45.848
<i>DEAN:
Welcome to our Concert in the Park...</i>

01:32:46.317 --> 01:32:51.380
...and the Mercedes Drive Your Future
Scholarship Celebration.

01:32:51.556 --> 01:32:54.218
And now it is with enormous pleasure...

01:32:54.392 --> 01:33:00.820
...that I welcome back to the concert stage
one of Juilliard's own, Lyla Novacek.

01:33:27.492 --> 01:33:32.020
[PLAYING DAVE METZGER'S
"CELLO CONCERTO IN E MINOR"]

01:33:55.420 --> 01:33:56.546
[LOUIS PLAYING LUCAS REYNOLDS'
"SOMETHING INSIDE"]

01:33:56.721 --> 01:33:59.656
<i>[SINGING]
So long you've been running in circles</i>

01:33:59.824 --> 01:34:01.689
<i>Round what's at stake</i>

01:34:04.729 --> 01:34:09.564
<i>But now the time's come
For your feet to stand still in one place</i>

01:34:13.104 --> 01:34:16.733
<i>You wanna reach out
You wanna give in</i>

01:34:16.908 --> 01:34:20.810
<i>Your head's wrapped around
What's around the next bend</i>

01:34:20.979 --> 01:34:26.246
<i>You wish you could find something warm
'Cause you're shivering cold</i>

01:34:28.853 --> 01:34:32.755
<i>It's the first thing you see
As you open your eyes</i>

01:34:32.924 --> 01:34:36.860
<i>The last thing you say
As you're saying goodbye</i>

01:34:37.028 --> 01:34:42.056
<i>But something inside you
Is crying, driving you on</i>

01:34:43.701 --> 01:34:48.035
<i>'Cause if you hadn't found me</i>

01:34:48.206 --> 01:34:50.640
<i>I would have found you</i>

01:34:52.510 --> 01:34:57.743
<i>I would have found you</i>

01:35:05.455 --> 01:35:07.184
I have to go now.

01:35:19.102 --> 01:35:20.899
I'm not coming back this time.

01:35:22.539 --> 01:35:23.870
He's just kidding, Wizard.

01:35:25.475 --> 01:35:28.205
Me and August have a understanding.
Don't we?

01:35:33.350 --> 01:35:35.545
Aug, you can't leave me, man.

01:35:35.719 --> 01:35:37.482
Yes, I can.

01:35:38.722 --> 01:35:40.849
Because you have to
find your parents, right?

01:35:41.024 --> 01:35:43.788
Yeah. My concert's starting.

01:35:43.960 --> 01:35:49.023
Well, all my money's on the fact
your folks won't be able to find you.

01:35:49.199 --> 01:35:50.530
You know why?

01:35:50.934 --> 01:35:52.834
Because they can't hear you.

01:35:53.270 --> 01:35:54.601
They're probably dead.

01:35:54.771 --> 01:35:56.966
You're not going anywhere.

01:36:00.811 --> 01:36:05.373
<i>It's the first thing you see
As you open your eyes</i>

01:36:05.582 --> 01:36:08.983
<i>The last thing you say
As you're saying goodbye</i>

01:36:09.186 --> 01:36:10.244
Nowhere to go, son.

01:36:10.420 --> 01:36:14.015
<i>Something inside you
Is crying and driving you on</i>

01:36:15.058 --> 01:36:20.860
<i>I would have found you</i>

01:36:21.298 --> 01:36:23.061
ARTHUR:
Run, boy.

01:36:23.233 --> 01:36:24.757
Run, August, run.

01:36:24.935 --> 01:36:28.871
<i>I would have found you</i>

01:36:31.208 --> 01:36:35.941
<i>I would have found you</i>

01:36:37.080 --> 01:36:39.275
[HORN HONKS]

01:36:45.889 --> 01:36:48.357
WALLACE:
August!

01:37:01.772 --> 01:37:04.866
[PLAYING DAVE METZGER'S
"CELLO CONCERTO IN E MINOR"]

01:37:38.475 --> 01:37:41.000
WALLACE:
August!

01:38:01.363 --> 01:38:03.991
DEAN:
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen.

01:38:04.366 --> 01:38:10.168
Music has always fascinated us
in the way that it communicates.

01:38:10.339 --> 01:38:13.365
Without words, without pictures.

01:38:14.276 --> 01:38:17.143
And that leads us
to our final performance.

01:38:21.317 --> 01:38:23.478
NICK:
How much longer to the airport?

01:38:23.652 --> 01:38:26.143
MARSHALL:
Man, it jams up the traffic.

01:38:26.322 --> 01:38:28.813
Bring you back to the old days,
eh, Louis?

01:38:30.960 --> 01:38:34.862
[MARK MANCINA'S
"ARPEGGIO THEME" PLAYING]

01:38:46.542 --> 01:38:48.339
"August Rush."

01:38:48.510 --> 01:38:50.341
Evan Taylor.

01:39:06.061 --> 01:39:10.725
